  <actrnumber>ACTRN12608000413325</actrnumber>
  <trial_identification>
    <studytitle>A feasibility study of a structured means of eliciting goals in rehabilitation</studytitle>
    <scientifictitle>In stroke patients undergoing inpatient rehabilitation does a structured approach to goal-setting compared to usual care improve life satisfaction or satisfaction with rehabilitation care</scientifictitle>
    <utrn />
    <trialacronym />
    <secondaryid>COPM study</secondaryid>
  </trial_identification>
  <conditions>
    <healthcondition>Stroke</healthcondition>
    <healthcondition>Disabling illness</healthcondition>
    <conditioncode>
      <conditioncode1>Physical Medicine / Rehabilitation</conditioncode1>
      <conditioncode2>Other physical medicine / rehabilitation</conditioncode2>
    </conditioncode>
  </conditions>
  <interventions>
    <interventions>The 'intervention' is administration of the Canadian Occupational Performance Measure in order to elicit goals in a structured means, with feed back of results (patient goals) to the clinical team. It is a single intervention spread over the course of a 45 minute interview and dissemination to the rehabilitation team over 72 hours.</interventions>
    <comparator>Usual care, which pragmatically will be the normal rehabilitation team care for that clinical service, including whatever approach to goal-setting is normally used.</comparator>
    <control>Active</control>
    <interventioncode>Rehabilitation</interventioncode>
  </interventions>
  <outcomes>
    <primaryOutcome>
      <outcome>Schedule for the Evaluation of  Individual Quality of Life</outcome>
      <timepoint>Discharge from hospital and 3 months later</timepoint>
    </primaryOutcome>
    <secondaryOutcome>
      <outcome>Patient perspective of care and rehabilitation (PaPeR 2.1)</outcome>
      <timepoint>Discharge and 3 months</timepoint>
    </secondaryOutcome>
    <secondaryOutcome>
      <outcome>Functional Independence Measure</outcome>
      <timepoint>Discharge and 3 months</timepoint>
    </secondaryOutcome>
    <secondaryOutcome>
      <outcome>SF-36v2 (Health Status)</outcome>
      <timepoint>Discharge and 3 months</timepoint>
    </secondaryOutcome>
  </outcomes>
  <eligibility>
